{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The method ","type":"text"},{"code":"sortedMerging","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can merge two sorted sequences:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["for x in [1, 3, 5].sortedMerging([2, 3, 4]) {","    print(x)","}","","\/\/ Prints 1","\/\/ Prints 2","\/\/ Prints 3","\/\/ Prints 3","\/\/ Prints 4","\/\/ Prints 5"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With dictionary-like sequences, it can also merge entries with the same key:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let julSales = [(\"Alex\", 10), (\"Bob\", 20)]","let augSales = [(\"Bob\", 20), (\"Carl\", 30)]","","let totalSales = julSales.sortedMerging(augSales) { $0.0 < $0.1 }","  areDuplicates: { $0.0 == $1.0 }","  mergeDuplicates: { ($0.0, $0.1 + $1.1) }","","for (person, sale) in totalSales {","    print(person, sale)","}","","\/\/ Prints \"Alex\" 10","\/\/ Prints \"Bob\" 40","\/\/ Prints \"Carl\" 30"]},{"text":"Parameters","anchor":"Parameters","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Other than the two sequences, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sortedMerging"},{"text":" methods take three parameters:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"areInAscendingOrder"},{"text":", which serves as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"<"},{"text":" in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Comparable"},{"text":" implementation.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"areDuplicates","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which serves as ","type":"text"},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in an ","type":"text"},{"code":"Equatable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" implementation. If you do not want to merge any pair of elements, simply return ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This is also the default implementation when no value is provided.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mergeDuplicates"},{"type":"text","text":", which merges elements identified as duplicates by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"areDuplicates"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"style":"important","type":"aside","name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The two input sequences must be sorted with respect to the provided "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"areInAscendingOrder"},{"type":"text","text":" for the result to be meaningful."}]}]},{"text":"Variants","anchor":"Variants","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are an eager version and a lazy version. The former takes non-escaping throwing closures, whereas the latter takes escaping non-throwing ones. You might be forced to use one of the two, given these constraints. If not, you can use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".lazy"},{"type":"text","text":" to use the lazy version."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your sequence’s element type conforms to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Comparable"},{"type":"text","text":", there is also a shortcut version that does not merge duplicates. It orders elements by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"<"},{"type":"text","text":", and returns a sequence that produces elements lazily."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Sorted Merge","modules":[{"name":"Yumi"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Yumi\/documentation\/Yumi\/SortedMerge","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Yumi\/documentation\/Yumi"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Merging two "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"sorted"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" sequences."}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/yumi\/sortedmerge"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://Yumi/documentation/Yumi":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Some commonly used functionality."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Yumi\/documentation\/Yumi","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Yumi","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/yumi"}}}